1
00:01:05,879 --> 00:01:07,280
I don't care what method you use,

2
00:01:07,640 --> 00:01:09,439
just find Da Zui for me.

3
00:01:10,079 --> 00:01:10,519
Go.

4
00:01:11,040 --> 00:01:11,840
Go.

5
00:01:13,040 --> 00:01:13,519
Yes.

6
00:01:15,319 --> 00:01:15,680
Dad.

7
00:01:16,239 --> 00:01:16,879
What's wrong?

8
00:01:18,400 --> 00:01:19,359
The goods were seized,

9
00:01:20,519 --> 00:01:21,599
and I was wanted.

10
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:24,640
It's all because of the Lu guy.

11
00:01:25,640 --> 00:01:27,959
The Xie's order was stopped,

12
00:01:29,040 --> 00:01:30,560
and I took the blame.

13
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:35,480
Don't see your thug boyfriend anymore.

14
00:01:36,879 --> 00:01:38,680
My boyfriend is not a thug.

15
00:01:38,959 --> 00:01:40,439
He's Lu Zhiyu's brother.

16
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:43,079
You've invited a wolf into your house.

17
00:01:43,879 --> 00:01:45,159
Don't see him again.

18
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:47,400
It was him who ruined my business.

19
00:01:48,079 --> 00:01:49,599
Who cares about your business?

20
00:01:50,159 --> 00:01:51,719
You only care about your business.

21
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:52,640
You don't care about me at all.

22
00:02:08,240 --> 00:02:09,680
I didn't run away yesterday because of you.

23
00:02:09,879 --> 00:02:11,240
It was because of the full moon.

24
00:02:12,879 --> 00:02:14,919
I didn't run away yesterday because of you.

25
00:02:15,439 --> 00:02:16,240
because of the Moon.

26
00:02:17,680 --> 00:02:18,199
No.

27
00:02:19,439 --> 00:02:20,919
I'm here to get my payment.

28
00:02:22,439 --> 00:02:23,159
No.

29
00:02:25,319 --> 00:02:26,319
It's her fault.

30
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:27,680
Why do I bother her?

31
00:02:30,919 --> 00:02:31,560
I'm so stupid.

32
00:02:55,039 --> 00:02:55,639
What's wrong?

33
00:02:55,840 --> 00:02:56,719
Who bullied you?

34
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:58,240
Qin Yeren.

35
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:03,599
Your father wants you to marry those nobles.

36
00:03:04,280 --> 00:03:05,080
It's understandable

37
00:03:05,639 --> 00:03:06,879
It's understandable.

38
00:03:07,919 --> 00:03:08,680
What's wrong?

39
00:03:09,039 --> 00:03:09,840
You're fine.

40
00:03:12,879 --> 00:03:13,879
I don't like those

41
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:15,319
rich second-generation.

42
00:03:15,599 --> 00:03:16,759
They're pretentious and gross.

43
00:03:17,919 --> 00:03:18,639
Even if

44
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:20,319
he sent 10,000 people after me,

45
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:21,800
I wouldn't go back to that family.

46
00:03:25,199 --> 00:03:26,360
Are you planning to live rough

47
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:28,159
with such heavy luggage?

48
00:03:29,759 --> 00:03:30,199
Exactly.

49
00:03:30,919 --> 00:03:32,080
I've been wanting to go camping for a long time.

50
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:33,960
I think

51
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:36,000
the woods we went to last time were pretty good.

52
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:38,039
I have to warn you,

53
00:03:38,479 --> 00:03:39,280
that woods

54
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:40,639
has snakes

55
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:41,479
and bugs,

56
00:03:41,759 --> 00:03:43,080
and you'll have to boil water and cook your own food.

57
00:03:45,960 --> 00:03:46,840
That sounds so exciting!

58
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:51,159
You were just crying and whining,

59
00:03:51,319 --> 00:03:52,680
and now you're all smiles.

60
00:03:54,080 --> 00:03:55,120
A girl's emotions

61
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:56,680
are naturally ever-changing.

62
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:00,000
But

63
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:01,240
I'm easy to please.

64
00:04:02,199 --> 00:04:03,360
When I'm angry

65
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:04,800
or upset,

66
00:04:05,560 --> 00:04:06,919
just a few compliments

67
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:08,520
will cheer me up.

68
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:19,199
You're going the wrong way.

69
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:22,120
It's none of your business.

70
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:50,879
Let me help you.

71
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:53,800
I don't need your help.

72
00:04:54,759 --> 00:04:56,600
I'll get used to living on my own.

73
00:04:57,439 --> 00:04:58,480
No matter where I was before,

74
00:04:58,759 --> 00:05:00,199
there were always a bunch of bodyguards following me.

75
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,160
They all listened to me.

76
00:05:03,160 --> 00:05:04,240
But actually, I know

77
00:05:04,839 --> 00:05:06,360
that without the identity of the Young Miss,

78
00:05:07,199 --> 00:05:08,560
no one really understands me,

79
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,920
and no one cares about me.

80
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:16,399
Someone will always care.

81
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:20,360
I mean,

82
00:05:21,879 --> 00:05:23,839
I always thought I was a lone wolf,

83
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:25,399
with the world as my home,

84
00:05:25,759 --> 00:05:26,439
and without any support.

85
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:28,199
But in the end,

86
00:05:29,560 --> 00:05:30,360
I found that life

87
00:05:30,439 --> 00:05:31,720
is not as lonely as I thought.

88
00:05:33,199 --> 00:05:35,519
I didn't expect your brother to raise you well.

89
00:05:39,439 --> 00:05:40,600
Are you coveting my brother?

90
00:05:41,399 --> 00:05:42,199
I'm not.

91
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:43,600
Don't look down on me.

92
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:50,399
Even if you don't go home,

93
00:05:50,759 --> 00:05:52,079
you don't have to live in the open air.

94
00:05:53,319 --> 00:05:54,040
You don't understand.

95
00:05:54,560 --> 00:05:55,040
If I live in a hotel,

96
00:05:55,079 --> 00:05:57,000
I will be caught by the people my father sent.

97
00:05:58,199 --> 00:05:59,600
I have no other choice.

98
00:06:03,399 --> 00:06:04,079
Actually...

99
00:06:08,759 --> 00:06:09,519
Nothing.

100
00:06:17,319 --> 00:06:18,160
Did you buy this?

101
00:06:19,399 --> 00:06:20,439
It's very suitable for me to wear.

102
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:22,879
This is a festival decoration.

103
00:06:23,319 --> 00:06:23,920
Festival?

104
00:06:24,439 --> 00:06:25,120
What festival?

105
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:26,959
In a few days,

106
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:29,519
it will be the Wolf Clan's Shuoyue Festival.

107
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:30,839
Every year on this festival,

108
00:06:31,279 --> 00:06:32,160
our relatives and friends

109
00:06:32,279 --> 00:06:33,040
will get together,

110
00:06:33,959 --> 00:06:36,319
and sing and dance on the beach.

111
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:38,560
Dance?

112
00:06:39,319 --> 00:06:40,519
Can you dance the hula?

113
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:41,480
I want to see you dance.

114
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:44,600
You'd better see A Che dance.

115
00:06:46,199 --> 00:06:46,800
A Che

116
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:50,600
Your brother wants you to dance the hula on the festival.

117
00:06:53,759 --> 00:06:54,319
A Che

118
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:55,720
Why are you so weird?

119
00:06:56,519 --> 00:06:57,319
What happened?

120
00:07:03,600 --> 00:07:05,800
I have a friend.

121
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:08,079
who has a friend

122
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:09,959
who recently had a falling out with his family.

123
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,079
He can't go home.

124
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:12,639
Anyway,

125
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:15,199
can we take her in?

126
00:07:19,560 --> 00:07:21,079
Who had a falling out with whom?

127
00:07:22,199 --> 00:07:23,560
Is your friend

128
00:07:23,639 --> 00:07:25,959
a wolf or a human?

129
00:07:27,399 --> 00:07:27,920
Human.

130
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:29,360
Male or female?

131
00:07:29,519 --> 00:07:30,040
Female.

132
00:07:32,759 --> 00:07:33,879
You have a girlfriend?

133
00:07:34,199 --> 00:07:35,439
No, no, no.

134
00:07:35,639 --> 00:07:36,120
Not me.

135
00:07:36,439 --> 00:07:36,959
Not me.

136
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:42,480
Then your friend's friend's friend.

137
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:44,600
Does she know you?

138
00:07:45,160 --> 00:07:48,079
Will she be a threat to the wolf clan?

139
00:07:48,199 --> 00:07:48,759
She

140
00:07:50,160 --> 00:07:51,680
doesn't seem to know me very well.

141
00:07:52,839 --> 00:07:53,800
Do you know her?

142
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:55,759
In other words,

143
00:07:55,959 --> 00:07:57,360
what do you think of her?

144
00:07:58,560 --> 00:07:59,800
She's always aloof.

145
00:08:00,199 --> 00:08:01,360
She looks down on everyone.

146
00:08:02,519 --> 00:08:04,639
She covers her loneliness by pretending to be cool.

147
00:08:05,639 --> 00:08:06,759
She is also simple and straightforward.

148
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:08,480
Sometimes,

149
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,120
she's a little bit silly.

150
00:08:11,319 --> 00:08:13,120
It sounds not bad.

151
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:15,120
It should be not bad.

152
00:08:16,519 --> 00:08:17,360
I vote for it.

153
00:08:18,360 --> 00:08:19,800
But you still have to be careful.

154
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:22,000
After all, she is still a human.

155
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:26,480
Then let A Che

156
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:28,240
stay with this friend more.

157
00:08:29,079 --> 00:08:30,040
If we don't know her well,

158
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:32,519
we can get to know her better.

159
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:36,840
Then I'll leave this task to you.

160
00:08:37,919 --> 00:08:38,360
Okay.

161
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:45,679
Did you cook like this before?

162
00:08:47,279 --> 00:08:47,840
No.

163
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:50,320
It's just that I suddenly realized

164
00:08:50,399 --> 00:08:52,639
that cooking seems to be

165
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:55,039
a profound science.

166
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:57,840
Learn well.

167
00:08:58,759 --> 00:08:59,559
I'll check it out.

168
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:06,559
Festival decorations.

169
00:09:09,200 --> 00:09:10,279
Don't smear it on my face.

170
00:09:11,279 --> 00:09:11,799
No.

171
00:09:13,159 --> 00:09:14,559
Don't smear it on my face.

172
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:16,759
Brother

173
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:21,320
She

174
00:09:21,759 --> 00:09:23,200
is the one you said...

175
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:26,200
She is my friend.

176
00:09:28,399 --> 00:09:30,120
The prank is over.

177
00:09:31,159 --> 00:09:32,200
Take her back.

178
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:33,960
I'm serious.

179
00:09:36,799 --> 00:09:38,000
I don't object to you making friends

180
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:41,240
with girls.

181
00:09:42,799 --> 00:09:44,120
But Qin Yaxin

182
00:09:44,519 --> 00:09:45,039
is not allowed.

183
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:48,799
What her father did

184
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:50,279
has nothing to do with her.

185
00:09:50,679 --> 00:09:51,159
Brother,

186
00:09:51,279 --> 00:09:52,320
didn't you teach me this?

187
00:09:53,039 --> 00:09:54,519
Even if we don't talk about her identity,

188
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:56,639
her motive is not right.

189
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:07,480
Don't look at me with the eyes of your rival in love.

190
00:10:09,759 --> 00:10:11,360
I don't like the big guy

191
00:10:12,519 --> 00:10:13,559
who is stupid.

192
00:10:15,159 --> 00:10:16,840
I also think A Che is more suitable for you.

193
00:10:18,919 --> 00:10:19,559
No.

194
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:21,279
It's not what you think.

195
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:22,159
I...

196
00:10:26,279 --> 00:10:28,320
I take back what I said about being Mrs. Lu.

197
00:10:28,759 --> 00:10:29,279
And,

198
00:10:29,639 --> 00:10:31,200
I'm not planning to live here for free.

199
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:33,000
When I get a job and earn money,

200
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:34,240
I'll definitely make up for the rent.

201
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:36,679
Although you've changed your target,

202
00:10:37,360 --> 00:10:38,720
you're still quite ambitious.

203
00:10:40,799 --> 00:10:41,240
Brother,

204
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:43,000
Qin Yaxin doesn't like you anymore.

205
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:44,360
Don't be self-righteous.

206
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:50,679
She has cut off her relationship with Qin Yeren.

207
00:10:50,919 --> 00:10:52,120
She has no home to go back to.

208
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:54,039
And it was me who invited her here.

209
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:55,639
If I go back on my word at this point,

210
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:57,240
what credibility does the Wolf Clan have?

211
00:11:02,399 --> 00:11:03,000
A Che,

212
00:11:05,120 --> 00:11:06,320
are you threatening me?

213
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:12,279
If you don't welcome me, forget it.

214
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:15,000
I won't beg anyone.

215
00:11:15,759 --> 00:11:16,399
Wait.

216
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:21,720
You are adaptable.

217
00:11:29,159 --> 00:11:29,960
Stop it!

218
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:31,000
I'll leave.

219
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:32,480
What's wrong with living in a tent?

220
00:11:40,519 --> 00:11:41,399
It's the festival.

221
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:42,679
Will you stop?
